PREP: CLEAN: Wash hands. Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt. CLEAN: Wash hands. COOK: In large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add chicken skin-side down; cover and cook 15 minutes. Turn chicken; add onion and sprinkle with marjoram. Cover; cook over medium heat 15 to 20 minutes longer or until onion is soft and internal juices of chicken run clear. (Or insert instant-read meat thermometer in thickest part of chicken. Temperature should read 180 degrees F.) SERVE: Serve with parslied potatoes and steamed broccoli, if desired. CHILL: Refrigerate leftovers immediately.